org.fcrepo.kernel.modeshape.services

Class BatchServiceImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fcrepo.kernel.modeshape.services.AbstractService
      • org.fcrepo.kernel.modeshape.services.BatchServiceImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BatchService

    @Component
public class BatchServiceImpl
extends AbstractService
implements BatchService
    This is part of the strawman implementation for Fedora batch operations This service implements a simple FedoraSession service which is able to create/commit/rollback FedoraSession objects. A Scheduled annotation is used for removing timed out operations
    Author:
    frank asseg, ajs6f, acoburn

        @Scheduled(fixedRate=1000L)
public void removeExpired()
